quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  77,1,"By those unleashed in succession{1},",footnotes:1:According to Al-Qurtubi, exegetes differed about whether this refers to winds or angels.
  77,2,"and by those storming turbulently{1}.",footnotes:1:According to Al-Qurtubi, the majority of exegetes mentioned that this refers to the winds.
  77,3,"By those scattering far and wide,"
  77,4,"and by those separating decisively,"
  77,5,"and by those casting a Reminder{1},",footnotes:1:According to Al-Qurtubi, the majority of exegetes mentioned that this refers to the angels.
  77,6,"excusing or warning––"
  77,7,"indeed, what you<sup>pl </sup>are promised is sure to come."
  77,8,"So when the stars are obliterated,"
  77,9,"and when the sky is fractured,"
  77,10,"and when the mountains are blown away,"
